model.instruction:
Please use modelica to help me implement a model named `NewtonCoolingDynamic`: Simulate the temperature change of a water under Newton's law of cooling. Among them, the initial temperature of water (`T0`) is 100 °C, the ambient temperature (`T_inf`) is 25 °C, the water meter area (`A`) is 1 square meter, the mass (`m`) is 1kg, the specific heat (`c_p`) is 4200 J/(kg.°C), and the convection cooling coefficient (`h`) is 767 W/(m2.°C). Use an initial equation to set `T` to `T0`. 20 seconds after the start of the simulation, the ambient temperature suddenly dropped to 0°C.

//modelica
```model NewtonCoolingDynamic

model.output:
model NewtonCoolingDynamic
  "Cooling example with fluctuating ambient conditions"
  // Types
  type Temperature=Real(unit="K", min=0);
  type ConvectionCoefficient=Real(unit="W/(m2.K)", min=0);
  type Area=Real(unit="m2", min=0);
  type Mass=Real(unit="kg", min=0);
  type SpecificHeat=Real(unit="J/(K.kg)", min=0);

  // Parameters
  parameter Temperature T0=100 "Initial temperature";
  parameter ConvectionCoefficient h=767 "Convective cooling coefficient";
  parameter Area A=1.0 "Surface area";
  parameter Mass m=1 "Mass of thermal capacitance";
  parameter SpecificHeat c_p=4200 "Specific heat";

  // Variables
  Temperature T_inf "Ambient temperature";
  Temperature T "Temperature";
initial equation
  T = T0 "Specify initial value for T";
equation
  if time<=0.5 then
    T_inf = 25 "Constant temperature when time<=0.5";
  else
    T_inf = 0 "Otherwise, increasing";
  end if;
  m*c_p*der(T) = h*A*(T_inf-T) "Newton's law of cooling";
end NewtonCoolingDynamic;

model.instruction:
We have a reservoir, and we want to keep the height of the water (`waterLevel`) in the reservoir at a target height (`target_height`) of 1m. The water height (`waterLevel`) in the pool is 0.2m at the beginning. Please use proportional control to implement the above control system (defining the altitude error as `error` and the control signal as `control`) and simulate the change of the water level in the pool over time with a proportional factor (`Kp`) of 1. Please help me implement a modelica model named `PController`.

//modelica
```model PController

model.output:
model PController
  parameter Real Kp = 1 "Proportional coefficient";
  parameter Real target_height = 1 "Target altitude";

  Real waterLevel(start=0.2) "Actual altitude";
  Real error "Altitude error";
  Real control "Control signal";

equation
  error = target_height - waterLevel;
  control = Kp * error;
  der(waterLevel) = control;

end PController;

model.instruction:
We have a container, and we want to keep the height of the water (`waterLevel`) in the container at a target height (`target_height`) of 1 meter. The water height (`waterLevel`) in the pool starts at 0.2m, and the pool will leak 0.1m per unit time. Use proportional integral control to implement the above control system (defining height error as `error`, and splitting the logic into proportional control `Pcontrol`, which handles the leak, and integral control `Icontrol`) and simulate the change of the water level over time, where the proportional coefficient (`Kp`) is 1 and the integral coefficient (`Ki`) is 0.5. Please help me implement a modelica model named `PIController`.

//modelica
```model PIController

model.output:
model PIController
  parameter Real Kp=1 "Proportional coefficient";
  parameter Real Ki=0.5 "Integral coefficient";
  parameter Real target_height=1 "Target altitude";

  Real waterLevel(start=0.2) "Actual altitude";
  Real error "Altitude error";
  Real Pcontrol "Proportional Control signal", Icontrol "Integral Control signal";

equation
  error = target_height - waterLevel;
  Pcontrol = Kp * error - 0.1;
  error = der(Icontrol/Ki);
  der(waterLevel) = Pcontrol + Icontrol;

end PIController;

model.instruction:
We have a container, and we want to keep the height of the water (`waterLevel`) in the container at a target height (`target_height`) of 1 meter. The water height (`waterLevel`) in the pool starts at 0.2m. Use proportional differential control to implement the above control system (defining the height error as `error`, and splitting the logic into proportional control `Pcontrol` and differential control `Dcontrol`) and simulate the change of the water level in the pool over time, where the proportional coefficient (`Kp`) is 1 and the differential coefficient (`Kd`) is 0.1. Please help me implement a modelica model named `PDController`.

//modelica
```model PDController

model.output:
model PDController
  parameter Real Kp=1 "Proportional coefficient";
  parameter Real Kd=0.1 "Differential coefficient";
  parameter Real target_height=1 "Target altitude";

  Real waterLevel(start=0.2) "Actual altitude";
  Real error "Altitude error";
  Real Pcontrol "Proportional Control signal", Dcontrol "Differential Control signal";

equation
  error = target_height - waterLevel;
  Pcontrol = Kp * error;
  Dcontrol = Kd * der(error);
  der(waterLevel) = Pcontrol + Dcontrol;

