We have a container, and we want to keep the height of the water (`waterLevel`) in the container at a target height (`target_height`) of 1 meter. The water height (`waterLevel`) in the pool starts at 0.2m, and the pool will leak 0.1m per unit time. Use PID control to implement the above control system (defining the height error as `error`, and splitting the logic into proportional control `Pcontrol` which handles the leak, integral control `Icontrol`, and differential control `Dcontrol`) and simulate the change of the water level in the pool over time with a proportional coefficient (`Kp`) of 1, an integral coefficient (`Ki`) of 0.2, and a differential coefficient (`Kd`) of 0.1. Please help me implement a modelica model named `PIDController`.

//modelica
```model PIDController

model.output:
model PIDController
  parameter Real Kp=1 "Proportional coefficient";
  parameter Real Ki=0.2 "Integral coefficient";
  parameter Real Kd=0.1 "Differential coefficient";
  parameter Real target_height=1 "Target altitude";

  Real waterLevel(start=0.2) "Actual altitude";
  Real error "Altitude error";
  Real Pcontrol "Proportional Control signal", Icontrol "Integral Control signal", Dcontrol "Differential Control signal";

equation
  error = target_height - waterLevel;
  Pcontrol = Kp * error-0.1;
  error = der(Icontrol/Ki);
  Dcontrol = Kd * der(error);
  der(waterLevel) = Pcontrol + Icontrol + Dcontrol;

end PIDController;

model.instruction:
Suppose we have a hydraulic system consisting of two oil storage tanks and a cylindrical connecting pipe. It is known that the density of oil (`rho`) in the tank is 0.2; The initial height of the liquid in the left tank (`H1`) is 0.4 and the cross-sectional area (`A1`) is 1; The initial height of the liquid in the right tank (`H2`) is 0.6 and the cross-sectional area (`A2`) is 2. The connection pipe has a length (`L`) of 0.1 and a diameter (`D`) of 0.2, and the dynamic viscosity (`mu`) of the oil is 2e-3. The model also calculates a flow coefficient (`c`) based on the pipe dimensions and viscosity. Please help me implement the modelica model named `TwoTanks` of this system, including equations for pressures (`P1`, `P2`), flow rate (`Q`), and the conservation of mass to determine the rate of change of the heights.

//modelica
```model TwoTanks

model.output:
model TwoTanks "Hydraulic system involving two tanks"
  import Modelica.Units.SI;

  //constants
  constant Real pi = Modelica.Constants.pi;
  constant Real g = Modelica.Constants.g_n;

  //parameters
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.Length L = 0.1 "Pipe length";
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.Length D = 0.2 "Pipe diameter";
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.Density rho = 0.2 "Fluid density";
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.DynamicViscosity mu = 2e-3;
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.Area A1 = 1.0 "Area of left tank";
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.Area A2 = 2.0 "Area of right tank";
  parameter Modelica.Units.SI.KinematicViscosity c = (pi*D^4)/(128*mu*L);

  //variables
  Modelica.Units.SI.Pressure P1,P2;
  Modelica.Units.SI.Length H1(start=0.4),H2(start=0.6);
  Modelica.Units.SI.VolumeFlowRate Q;

equation
  //Pressure equations
  P1 = rho*H1*g;
  P2 = rho*H2*g;

  //Flow rate
  Q = c*(H1-H2);

  //conservation of mass
  A1*der(H1) = -Q;
  A2*der(H2) = Q;

end TwoTanks;

