Please simulate the temperature change of a platinum resistance sensor in a medium. It is known that the temperature of the measured medium (`Tg`) is stable at 100°C. The volume of the sensor (`V`) is 1.15*10^(-9), the comprehensive specific heat (`c`) is 456, the sensor surface area (`Ar`) is 5.31*10^(-6), the convective heat transfer coefficient (`alpha`) is 800, and the comprehensive density (`pho`) is 7980. The initial temperature of the sensor (`Tj`) is 25 °C. Please help me realize the Modelica model named `RTD_Pt100` where the medium temperature (`Tg`) is defined as an **input** and the sensor temperature (`Tj`) is defined as an **output**. The model should calculate the temperature change of the sensor over time based on the heat balance between the sensor and the medium.

//modelica
```model RTD_Pt100

model.output:
model RTD_Pt100 "A Thermal resistance temperature measurement model"

  //type
  type Time = Real (unit="s");
  type Voltage = Real(unit = "V");
  type Volume = Real(unit = "m3");
  type Density = Real(unit = "kg/m3", min = 0.0);
  type Current = Real(unit = "A");
  type Resistance = Real(unit = "Ohm");
  type Area = Real(unit = "m2");
  type ThermodynamicTemperature = Real(unit = "℃");
  type CoefficientOfHeatTransfer = Real(unit = "W/(m2.K)");
  type SpecificHeatCapacity = Real(unit = "J/(kg.K)");

  //parameters
  input ThermodynamicTemperature Tg(start=100) "Temperature of the medium to be measured";
  parameter Volume V=1.15*10^(-9) "Sensor volume";
  parameter SpecificHeatCapacity c=456 "The combined specific heat capacity of the sensor";
  parameter Area Ar=5.31*10^(-6) "Surface area of sensor";
  parameter CoefficientOfHeatTransfer alpha=800 "Surface heat exchange coefficient between sensor and medium";
  parameter Density pho=7980 "Sensor synthesis and density";
  output ThermodynamicTemperature Tj(start=25) "Sensor temperature";

