model LimitedActuator "An actuator with lag and saturation"
  extends Interfaces.Actuator;
  parameter Modelica.SIunits.Time delayTime
 "Delay time of output with respect to input signal";
  parameter Real uMax "Upper limits of input signals";
protected
  Modelica.Mechanics.Rotational.Sources.Torque torque(useSupport=true)
 ;
  Modelica.Blocks.Nonlinear.Limiter limiter(uMax=uMax)
 ;
  Modelica.Blocks.Nonlinear.FixedDelay lag(delayTime=delayTime)
 ;
equation
  connect(torque.flange, shaft) ;
  connect(torque.support, housing) ;
  connect(limiter.y, torque.tau) ;
  connect(lag.u, tau) ;
  connect(lag.y, limiter.u) 
  ;
end LimitedActuator;

model.instruction:
Generate a Modelica model named `PID_Controller` for a PID (Proportional-Integral-Derivative) Controller subsystem. The model should:

1. Extends the `ModelicaByExample.Architectures.SensorComparison.Interfaces.Controller`.
2. The model includes the following parameters :
 - Real 'k' is Gain of controller;
 -Modelica.SIunits.Time 'Ti' is Time constant of Integrator block;
 - Modelica.SIunits.Time 'Td' isTime constant of Derivative block;
 - Real 'yMax' is Upper limit of output.
3. Utilize a 'Modelica.Blocks.Continuous.LimPID' block named 'PID' in the protected section, configured with specific parameters for controller gain (k), time constant of the Integrator block (Ti), time constant of the Derivative block (Td), and an upper limit of output (yMax).
4. Establish the following signal connections in the equation section: The reference tracking connects the external setpoint to the PID block's setpoint input (PID.u_s).
The feedback loop links the measured signal to the PID block's measurement input (PID.u_m).
The control action is routed from the PID block's output (PID.y) to the external command interface.

//modelica
```model PID_Controller

model.output:
model PID_Controller "Controller subsystem implemented using a PID controller"
  extends Interfaces.Controller;
  parameter Real k "Gain of controller";
  parameter Modelica.SIunits.Time Ti "Time constant of Integrator block";
  parameter Modelica.SIunits.Time Td "Time constant of Derivative block";
  parameter Real yMax "Upper limit of output";
protected
  Modelica.Blocks.Continuous.LimPID PID(k=k, Ti=Ti, Td=Td, yMax=yMax)
 ;
equation
  connect(setpoint, PID.u_s) ;
  connect(measured, PID.u_m) ;
  connect(PID.y, command) 
  ;
end PID_Controller;

