//modelica
```model OnOffVariant

model.output:
model ClassicModel "This is the typical equation-oriented model"
  parameter Real alpha=0.1 "Reproduction rate of prey";
  parameter Real beta=0.02 "Mortality rate of predator per prey";
  parameter Real gamma=0.4 "Mortality rate of predator";
  parameter Real delta=0.02 "Reproduction rate of predator per prey";
  parameter Real x0=10 "Start value of prey population";
  parameter Real y0=10 "Start value of predator population";
  Real x(start=x0) "Prey population";
  Real y(start=y0) "Predator population";
equation
  der(x) = x*(alpha-beta*y);
  der(y) = y*(delta*x-gamma);
end ClassicModel;

model.instruction:
Generate a Modelica block that computes feedback terms. The model should have two 'ModelicaByExample.Components.BlockDiagrams.Interfaces.RealInput' (u1 and u2) and one 'ModelicaByExample.Components.BlockDiagrams.Interfaces.RealOutput' (y). The equation for the output y is the difference between the inputs u1 and u2. The model should be based on Modelica version 3.2.3 and be named `Feedback`.

//modelica
```block Feedback

model.output:
block Feedback "A block to compute feedback terms"
  Interfaces.RealInput u1
 ;
  Interfaces.RealInput u2 ;
  Interfaces.RealOutput y
 ;
equation
  y = u1-u2
  ;
end Feedback;

